        ],
        "content": "## TIØ4145 Corporate Finance Fall 2021 Exam – Answers to the multiple-choice questions\n\n## Sustainable Finance\n\nThe two dimensions of sustainability reporting are a) the impact in shareholder assessment and decisions, and b) significance on economic, social and environmental impacts.\n\n## Valuation of Bonds\n\nP = $52.50/1.058 + $52.50/1.0552 + $52.50/1.0523 + $1052.50/1.0504 = $1007.78 which is greater than $1000, so it trades at a premium.\n\n## Capital Budgeting\n\nThe tax shield will last for $320 million/($100 million × 0.80) = 4.0 years.\n\n## Debt Markets\n\nThe expected loss of lending can be calculated by multiplying the probability of default, the value of loss given a default and the exposure of the lender at default.\n\n## Valuation of Companies\n\nIf a company goes through a stable business cycle, the normalized earnings method is a common choice.\n\nReal Options 1 – create value with real options\n\nOptimally delaying or abandoning projects\n\nReal Options 2 – NPV of the project\n\nAnswer: 90,000.\n\n## CAPM 1 – not an assumption\n\nInvestors have homogeneous risk-averse preferences toward taking on risk.\n\n## CAPM 2 – consistent with CAPM\n\nA security with only systematic risk has an expected return that exceeds the risk-free interest rate.\n\n## Fama-French-Carhart model\n\nAnswer: 0.53%",
        "embed": "## TIØ4145 Corporate Finance Fall 2021 Exam – Answers to the multiple-choice questions\n\n## Sustainable Finance\n\nThe two dimensions of sustainability reporting are a) the impact in shareholder assessment and decisions, and b) significance on economic, social and environmental impacts.\n\n## Valuation of Bonds\n\nP = $52.50/1.058 + $52.50/1.0552 + $52.50/1.0523 + $1052.50/1.0504 = $1007.78 which is greater than $1000, so it trades at a premium.\n\n## Capital Budgeting\n\nThe tax shield will last for $320 million/($100 million × 0.80) = 4.0 years.\n\n## Debt Markets\n\nThe expected loss of lending can be calculated by multiplying the probability of default, the value of loss given a default and the exposure of the lender at default.\n\n## Valuation of Companies\n\nIf a company goes through a stable business cycle, the normalized earnings method is a common choice.\n\nReal Options 1 – create value with real options\n\nOptimally delaying or abandoning projects\n\nReal Options 2 – NPV of the project\n\nAnswer: 90,000.\n\n## CAPM 1 – not an assumption\n\nInvestors have homogeneous risk-averse preferences toward taking on risk.\n\n## CAPM 2 – consistent with CAPM\n\nA security with only systematic risk has an expected return that exceeds the risk-free interest rate.\n\n## Fama-French-Carhart model\n\nAnswer: 0.53%",
